track.name: Hobo Blues
comments: On the second album i ever bought....Jerry Lee "Best Of" first. Was about 16...had the Blues ever since!!
Hooker kicks ass and doesn't bother with takin names.
Now we are cookin' with gas !!!  In the Hobo's case,sterno or even a sterno log.
You hear the blues by Hooker, and you've heard the real Blues. He's one of the rocks of Truth that all the wannabes brake against.
I JUST LOVE MYSELF SOME GOOD OLD BLUES

I don't listen to blues.  I really know nothing about blues.  But I stumbled onto a live version of this song a few hours ago and it was one of the most brilliant performances I have ever experienced.
Diesen Song muß man ganz einfach lieben .....  John Lee Hooker einer der ganz "Großen" ....... !!!
Once old timers like this die out, will this original style die out as well. Hope not!
I can just see John Hooker hitchin a train right now.
not listened to jlh for a long time i'm ashamed will try to make up for it a legend
i love it when lastfm radio skips the song after a few secs and i drop in and go wow
HOBO, HEALER, = BIG JOHN LEE HOOKER
